info.headline: High Wind Warning issued September 23 at 2:05AM MDT until September 23 at 3:00PM MDT by NWS Cheyenne
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 PM MDT THIS AFTERNOON... * WHAT...West winds 35 to 50 MPH with gusts up to 80 MPH expected. * WHERE...South Laramie Range and South Laramie Range Foothills including Interstate 80 between Laramie and Cheyenne. * WHEN...Until 3 PM MDT this afternoon. The strongest winds are expected around sunrise. * IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Strong cross winds will be hazardous to light weight or high profile vehicles, including campers and tractor trailers.
info.instruction: A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage.
